<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-30T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-30T06:44:00-05:00" n="703" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d703">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">853i.79682/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-30T11:00:00-00:44">December 30, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 11:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>93. Referring to the Department’s No. 60, December 27. Pan American
                                Airways had acceded to Liberian Government’s original demand that
                                monopolistic clause be excluded. In the final draft of contract
                                President Barclay incorporated monopolistic clause and stipulated
                                that company furnish services within 1 year. Because concessionaires
                                failed in the past to exercise rights President Barclay reasons that
                                a specific time limit would mean nothing to Pan American Airways
                                unless granted a monopoly.<note n="10" xml:id="d703fn10">Contract as
                                    amended finally was signed at Monrovia, July 14, 1941</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>